 new policy tool, such funds would ensure that more of the gains from economic activity are shared by all and not colonised by a powerful few. This is a vital new contribution to the pressing debate on how to reduce inequality and combat austerity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aInvestment of public fundszGreat Britain. 0aPublic investmentszGreat Britain. 0aSovereign wealth funds. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z9783111196435oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144733143840uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447331445?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447331445423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447331445/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2016